10:
Yeah. It's brimming with cream!
...Are you going to demand some
as an offering, or...
15:
Do you take me for a miser? I wished
only to know where you bought it!
19: ...Tutor! So this is where you were!
21:
Your highness! It is a relief to see you
safe!
25: My purse! Where is my purse?!
34:
Sounds like quite the hullabaloo... Well,
what do I always say? The only thing
Prince Razelt can find his way to...
is trouble.
36: Well, if you would stop disappearing!
39:
Okay, let's stop trying to place the
blame, and be happy you found
each other.
42:
You speak wisely. Tell me, Tutor, how
were your travels? Were they as great
as my own?
45:
I have become... well-acquainted with
the nightlife of various cities... but that's
a story for a different time. I have a
favor to ask of you.
46:
Your younger brother will soon be
leaving for his first trial. He wishes to see
you before then.
54: As have I. I am glad to see you well.
57: Is he a soldier of your guard?
61:
No, he is Alkâ€”my friend and a seasoned
traveler with many tales to tell.
64:
A friend! Should the chance arise, I do
hope you'll share your tales with me.
67:
Your brother's exaggerating... But I'd be
more than happy to chat sometime,
your highness.
72:
...Now. I heard you will soon face your
first trial.
76:
Yes. The second of the Nine Houses
put forth that I would not be fit to lead
until I proved myself in battle.
78:
The Dau? They direct finance! What
business do they have, demanding
you risk your life!
80:
Did they not pledge their allegiance
to you?
82:
Brother. I have long hoped for a chance
to show my worth.
85:
You must understand. I do not go
needlessly into peril.
86:
The trial is tomorrow, the foe a dragon.
I humbly request your presence.
90:
But he's just a kid!
He can't fight a dragon, Razelt.
94:
No, he cannot...
I have come to a crossroads...
99:
...May fortune smile upon you.
Now, let the trial begin!
101:
Tsk! It's too strong!
This really was a plotâ€”
107:
For honor and country, I call upon thee!
Ward thy people, Lord's Aegis!
110:
Y-your highness! What are you doing?
Surely you must know that your
actionsâ€”
113:
And you call yourself a guard...
You would endanger YOUR ward
and MY brother for politics?!
115:
If it is a prince's duty to cast aside
family for vain ambition, then
I renounce my title!
116:
Armor may crack, and my Lord's Aegis
may shatter! But as long as I am Razelt,
I will deliver my brother to victory!
118:
Though I would prefer to do it in one
piece... Dragon, cease your flames!
121:
Brother! You must withdraw! Not even
you can fell the dragon!
125:
No, I cannot. Not alone. But with the
aid of a friend... Now, Alk!
132:
Good work, Razelt.
You looked pretty cool out there.
135:
Of course. There is nothing "cooler"
than protecting your family.
143:
I am sorry. But I could not just stand by
and watch!
145:
Don't apologize. I was happy you
defended me. Thank you, Brother!
146:
To tell the truth, I had hoped you would
save me... And I accomplished what
I set out to do...
149: Y-you did? Then I am glad for you.
151:
However, I wish my Lord's Aegis had
not been shattered...
155:
I mean, without your magic shield,
you really are just a stray puppy...
163:
Your Highness. I actually have a spot
of good news for you.
166:
What you call fair tidings, I call an
ill omen.
168:
Oh? Then I suppose you won't be
wanting this after all.
170:
That was quick. But then again,
the Oinas are a powerful family.
176:
Let's just say, I had an inkling you'd
need a new one... As did your younger
brother.
177:
Hehe. And our finance minister
is beholden to me.
178:
And thus, Your Highness, you've
escaped the life of a stray... for now.
181:
Am I a prince, or the court fool?!
...Wait. Do not answer that question.
185:
Alk, I have made my choice. Starview
Village shall be my home for a while
longer. The castle walls now feel like
a cage to me!
188:
Sureâ€”as long as you know there's
no such thing as a free meal.
Hope you're ready to work, Razelt!
